---
import Layout from '@/components/chrome/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Disclosures — STR Host Tools"
  description="Affiliate, advertising, and editorial disclosures for strhost.tools."
  path="/disclosures"
>
  <section class="bg-parchment">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-12 pb-9">
      <p class="label text-gold-deep">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-h1 font-serif text-navy leading-tight">
        Disclosures<span class="period-gold">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lead text-ink-2">
        Full disclosures are in development. Here's the short version of how strhost.tools makes money and stays editorially honest.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-parchment-light border-t border-rule">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-9 prose">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-navy">Advertising</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-body text-ink-2 leading-snug">
        Calculator pages may display Google AdSense ads. Ad placement does not influence the formulas, data, or recommendations on this site.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-7 font-serif text-h2 text-navy">Affiliate links</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-body text-ink-2 leading-snug">
        Some outbound links to host tools, software, or services may be affiliate links. We only link to products the team has used or vetted. Affiliate revenue does not change the editorial position of the post.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-7 font-serif text-h2 text-navy">Sister product</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-body text-ink-2 leading-snug">
        strhost.tools is built and operated by the team at <a href="https://thestrledger.com" class="text-navy">The STR Ledger</a>. Soft cross-promotion appears in the footer and below-the-fold CTAs on tool pages. Tools and content are free; The STR Ledger is a paid product.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-7 font-serif text-h2 text-navy">Data sources</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-body text-ink-2 leading-snug">
        Lodging-tax rates are sourced annually from each state's Department of Revenue. Source URLs are linked on every state page. Other formulas and rate assumptions are documented on the relevant calculator page.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-7 text-caption text-ink-3 italic">
        Last updated: this stub is a placeholder. See <a href="/privacy" class="text-navy">Privacy</a> and <a href="/terms" class="text-navy">Terms</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
